6:
Sh-Shroombo, could you please
relax a little bit more?
11:
Shroombo, are you really that
excited to get your portrait painted?
Or... Oh! Are you embarrassed?
18:
I'm not sure I get the appeal of
painting the ocean. There's nothing
out there but blue on blue.
22:
Painting scenery requires a different
sort of skill set than I'm used to. This
should prove to be good practice.
27: Well... If it works for you, I guess...
38:
Approaching strangers in the street
is pretty difficult...
42:
*sigh* You get shy at the weirdest
times, you know that?
51: Guess there's no way around it...
54:
Come on, you've got a customer.
Better than none at all, yeah?
64:
...So this painting thing. Why do you
do it?
68: Well... I'm an artist. It's what I do.
70:
I can't live unless I'm creating, no
matter how much I have to suffer for
it.
74:
Huh. You duty-bound to paint or
something?
81: Did I give the impression that I am?
84: Sure sounded that way to me.
91:
Once I decided to commit myself to
art, I started feeling like I HAD to
paint. I couldn't stop, not if I wanted
to improve.
93:
I guess... somewhere along the way,
it became a responsibility weighing
down on my shoulders.
97:
I probably let Ryouki's opinion of me
get to my head, as well.
100:
Pressuring myself to progress
further and become the perfect role
model...
104:
Don't look at me. I dunno what
you're goin' on about.
Still though...
107:
My first hunch about you was
right.
You're a weird one.
111:
Am I? I don't think anybody's called
me that before.
114:
Sounds to me like you're surrounded
by people just as weird as you then...
128:
Okay, yelling at him won't work, so
I'm out of ideas. You got any?
133:
Um, well... I might have something to
cheer him up with...
136:
Look very closely.
Rise from your slumber...
142:
I can do other creatures too. Do you
have any ones you want to see?
145: Oh, oh! I wanna see a dragon!
148:
A-a dragon, huh... I'll see what I can
do!
157:
Thank you so much for looking after
my boy.
Say goodbye now, son.
162:
Goodbye. Try to stick by your
mother, okay?
170:
I just... never thought my art could
help someone like that.
172:
Painting was always something I did
for myself, so... It's weird to be
appreciated for it.
176:
I feel ready to tackle more!
But first... Would you like to keep this
painting?
180:
Heh... You're weird, but you're also a
softie, huh?
186:
But... That's a really punchable smirk.
Is this really what I look like?
190:
Yes. I simply paint things the way
they are.
